        </svg>
        <div class="interlude-title">As is <em>above,</em><br>so is <em>below.</em></div>
        <div class="interlude-body">The laws that govern the cosmos govern your breath, your digestion, your emotion, your thought. Self mastery is not a human invention. It is a universal principle.</div>
        <hr class="interlude-rule">
        <div class="interlude-quote">Every atom in your body was forged in a star.<br>You are not separate from the cosmos.<br>You are the cosmos, remembering itself.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">—</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 9: CH3 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-8">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Three</div>
        <div class="page-title">Your <em>Prakriti</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">Self mastery begins with knowing your original design.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <svg class="chapter-geo geo" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="80" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.25"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="50" r="54" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.4"/>
          <circle cx="53.3" cy="125" r="54" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.4"/>
          <circle cx="146.7" cy="125" r="54" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.9" opacity="0.4"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="4" fill="#7B2FBE"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="item-list">
          <div><div class="item-key">Vata, Space + Air</div><div class="item-desc">The intelligence of movement. Quick, light, expansive, visionary. When imbalanced: anxious, scattered, depleted.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Pitta, Fire + Water</div><div class="item-desc">The intelligence of transformation. Sharp, focused, courageous. When imbalanced: inflamed, critical, controlling.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Kapha, Water + Earth</div><div class="item-desc">The intelligence of cohesion. Grounded, nurturing, loyal. When imbalanced: stagnant, resistant, heavy.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">The Self Mastery Principle</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Your constitution is not a problem to fix. Self mastery asks you to understand your nature so deeply that you work with it, not against it.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">9</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 10: CH4 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-9">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Four</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Five <em>Laws</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">The universal principles that make self mastery possible.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <svg class="chapter-geo geo" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="82" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.2"/>
          <g opacity="0.45" stroke="#7B2FBE" fill="none">
            <circle cx="140" cy="100" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="120" cy="69.3" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="80" cy="69.3" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="60" cy="100" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="80" cy="130.7" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="120" cy="130.7" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
            <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="40" stroke-width="0.9"/>
          </g>
          <polygon points="100,22 172,110 28,110" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="1.3" opacity="0.7"/>
          <polygon points="100,178 172,90 28,90" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="1.3" opacity="0.7"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="4" fill="#7B2FBE"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="item-list">
          <div><div class="item-key">I, Correspondence</div><div class="item-desc">As above, so below. What is within you is reflected without.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">II, Vibration</div><div class="item-desc">Nothing is still. Self mastery is the practice of becoming coherent.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">III, Cause & Effect</div><div class="item-desc">Every action plants a seed. Every moment is a new beginning.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">IV, Polarity</div><div class="item-desc">Self mastery is not eliminating your shadow, it is integrating your full spectrum.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">V, Rhythm</div><div class="item-desc">Everything flows in cycles. Learn to move with them.</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">13</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 11: INTERLUDE 2 -->
    <div class="page interlude-page hidden" id="page-10">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <svg class="interlude-geo geo" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="84" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.5" opacity="0.2"/>
          <g opacity="0.45" stroke="#7B2FBE" fill="none" stroke-width="0.9">
            <circle cx="140" cy="100" r="40"/><circle cx="120" cy="69.3" r="40"/>
            <circle cx="80" cy="69.3" r="40"/><circle cx="60" cy="100" r="40"/>
            <circle cx="80" cy="130.7" r="40"/><circle cx="120" cy="130.7" r="40"/>
            <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="40"/>
          </g>
          <line x1="60" y1="100" x2="140" y2="100" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.7"/>
          <line x1="80" y1="65.4" x2="120" y2="134.6" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.7"/>
          <line x1="120" y1="65.4" x2="80" y2="134.6" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.7"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="4" fill="#7B2FBE"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="interlude-title">You are not finding yourself.<br>You are <em>remembering.</em></div>
        <div class="interlude-body">Self mastery is not construction. It is excavation. You are not building something new, you are uncovering something ancient that was always here.</div>
        <hr class="interlude-rule">
        <div class="interlude-quote">The self, understood fully, reveals the universe.<br>The universe, understood fully, reveals the self.<br>This is self mastery.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">—</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 12: CH5 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-11">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Five</div>
        <div class="page-title">Cosmology &amp; <em>Dharma</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">Self mastery is alignment with your deepest nature.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">Dharma is the intrinsic law of your being. The unique expression of self mastery that only you can bring into the world.</div>
        <div class="item-list">
          <div><div class="item-key">◌ Vata Dharma</div><div class="item-desc">Built for vision and communication. Channel restless energy into revelation, seeing what others cannot yet see.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">△ Pitta Dharma</div><div class="item-desc">Built for transformation and leadership. Direct sharp intelligence as service, not domination.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">◯ Kapha Dharma</div><div class="item-desc">Built for nurturing and sustaining. Learn to move, release, and let deep love flow rather than stagnate.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pull-quote"><p>When you stop fighting your nature, you stop leaking energy. What flows from alignment is not effort. It is dharmic power.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">17</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 13: CH6 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-12">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Six</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Practice of <em>Becoming</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">Self mastery is lived, not learned.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="item-list">
          <div><div class="item-key">Dinacharya</div><div class="item-desc">The sacred daily rhythm. How you begin the day is how you live your life.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Agni</div><div class="item-desc">Tend your digestive fire. Eat your largest meal at midday. Fast 12 hours each night.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Pranayama</div><div class="item-desc">Breathing as intelligence. Ten minutes each morning shifts the entire day.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Rasayana</div><div class="item-desc">The art of cellular renewal. The deepest rasayana is the quality of your attention and rest.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Sat-Sang</div><div class="item-desc">Self mastery is not a solo practice. Choose your environment as carefully as you choose your food.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">Integration Principle</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Self mastery is not adding more to your life, it is removing what was never aligned with your nature. The result is not discipline. It is coherence.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">21</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 14: CH7 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-13">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Seven</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Greatest <em>Activism</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">The highest expression of self mastery is planetary.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">Self mastery, fully understood, is not a private achievement. It is a public act. The work of becoming whole does not stay private. It ripples outward.</div>
        <div class="pull-quote"><p>The most radical act of activism is the embodiment of self mastery. A human being living in full alignment is a force of healing so powerful it cannot be measured. Only felt.</p></div>
        <div class="body-text">Artificial intelligence is beginning to mirror the intelligence of living systems, the five elements, the five laws, the patterns of coherence now playing out in neural networks and global economies.</div>
        <div class="body-text"><strong>Intelligence recognizes intelligence. The deeper we go into the science of life, the more we find the same breathtaking unity.</strong></div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">The Vision</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Imagine a world where constitutional diversity was understood as ecological richness. Every person who chooses evolution over fixation moves all of us closer to it.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">25</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 15: CH8 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-14">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Eight</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Morning <em>Intelligence</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">How you begin the day is how you live your life.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">The morning is the only time of day that belongs entirely to you. Everything after the first notification belongs to the world. <strong>The morning belongs to you. Use it.</strong></div>
        <div class="body-text">In Ayurveda, the early morning hours, <em>Brahma Muhurta</em>, are the most sattvic time of day. The mind is fresh. The nervous system is rested. What you do in these hours sets the tone for everything that follows.</div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">Your Constitutional Morning</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Vata: oil massage, warm food, no screens. Pitta: meditate before messages, no competitive thinking before 9am. Kapha: vigorous movement, stimulating breath, cold water. All: 10 minutes of silence before the day begins.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">Begin with one practice. Hold it for thirty days. Your nervous system will never forget.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">29</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 16: CH9 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-15">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Nine</div>
        <div class="page-title">Feed the <em>Fire</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">What you eat either builds you or depletes you.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">Food is not fuel. In Ayurveda, food is medicine, memory, and intelligence. Your body receives all of it.</div>
        <div class="pull-quote"><p>You can eat the most nutritious food in the world and still be malnourished if your Agni is weak. Digestion is not what happens in your stomach. It is what happens in every cell.</p></div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">The Six Tastes</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Sweet, Sour, Salty, Pungent, Bitter, Astringent. A meal including all six satisfies the body at a deep level, reducing cravings, supporting digestion, nourishing all tissues.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">The most radical nutritional change you can make: <strong>eat your largest meal at midday</strong> and make dinner the lightest meal of the day. Within two weeks, most people report better sleep, clearer skin, more stable energy.</div>
        <div class="body-text" style="font-style:italic">Feed the fire. Watch everything change.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">33</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 17: CH10 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-16">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Ten</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Emotional <em>Body</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">Your emotions are not problems. They are messages.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">Your emotional patterns are constitutional. The anxiety you have felt your whole life is not a character flaw, it is the shadow side of Vata's extraordinary gift.</div>
        <div class="pull-quote"><p>You are not broken. Your emotions are not broken. They are constitutionally calibrated signals, and when you understand what they are telling you, they stop controlling you.</p></div>
        <div class="item-list">
          <div><div class="item-key">Vata, Fear & Anxiety</div><div class="item-desc">Remedy: warmth, grounding, stillness. The anxious Vata needs their nervous system to feel held.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Pitta, Anger & Frustration</div><div class="item-desc">Remedy: cooling, surrender, time in nature. The enraged Pitta needs to put down the fire.</div></div>
          <div><div class="item-key">Kapha, Grief & Heaviness</div><div class="item-desc">Remedy: movement, literally and figuratively. Stagnant emotion needs circulation to release.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text" style="font-style:italic">That gap between stimulus and response is where self mastery lives.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">37</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 18: CH11 -->
    <div class="page hidden" id="page-17">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Chapter Eleven</div>
        <div class="page-title">The Relationships That <em>Heal You</em></div>
        <div class="page-tagline">You cannot self-master in isolation.</div>
        <hr class="page-rule">
        <div class="body-text">Self mastery is not a solo practice. The quality of your relationships is as important to your health as the quality of your food.</div>
        <div class="pull-quote"><p>The ancient practice of Sat-Sang, surrounding yourself with people of aligned consciousness, is not spiritual elitism. It is constitutional medicine.</p></div>
        <div class="body-text"><strong>You become, neurologically and biologically, a composite of the people you spend the most time with.</strong></div>
        <div class="insight-box">
          <div class="insight-label">The Ecology of Your Inner Circle</div>
          <div class="insight-text">Do you feel more like yourself or less after time with them? Do they call you higher or confirm your limitations? Sat-Sang is choosing relationships that support your evolution.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">Your healed nervous system heals the nervous systems around you. <strong>Show up whole. Let others remember they can too.</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="page-num">41</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 19: CLOSING -->
    <div class="page closing-page hidden" id="page-18">
      <div class="page-inner">
        <svg style="width:100px;height:100px;margin:0 auto" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="82" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.35"/>
          <g opacity="0.55" stroke="#7B2FBE" fill="none">
            <polygon points="100,28 164,110 36,110" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <polygon points="100,172 164,90 36,90" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <polygon points="100,48 148,120 52,120" stroke-width="0.8"/>
            <polygon points="100,152 148,80 52,80" stroke-width="0.8"/>
            <polygon points="100,65 138,128 62,128" stroke-width="0.6"/>
            <polygon points="100,135 138,72 62,72" stroke-width="0.6"/>
          </g>
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="14" fill="none" stroke="#7B2FBE" stroke-width="0.8" opacity="0.5"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="100" r="4" fill="#7B2FBE"/>
        </svg>
        <div class="closing-intro">You picked up this book because something in you remembered what you had forgotten.</div>
        <div>
          <div class="closing-title">You Are Not Broken.<br>You Are <em>Whole</em> <span class="closing-circle"></span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="closing-sub">Whole by original design. Intelligent by nature.<br><em>Self mastery is simply the practice of living that.</em></div>
        <hr class="closing-rule">
        <div class="closing-stinger">Every answer you searched for outside yourself<br>was pointing back toward the same place.<br>Every teacher, every system, every moment of grace<br>was the universe showing you what you already are.</div>
        <div class="closing-conclusion">Now you know the way home.</div>
        <hr class="closing-rule">
        <div class="closing-byline">Self Mastery · Evolution · The High Road</div>
        <div class="closing-author">chandanni miglino</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div><!-- end book -->
</div><!-- end wrapper -->

<button class="nav-btn nav-next" id="nextBtn" onclick="nextPage()">›</button>

<div class="page-counter" id="pageCounter">1 of 19</div>
<div class="touch-hint">swipe or tap arrows to turn pages</div>

<script>
const TOTAL = 19;
let current = 0;
let isAnimating = false;

const pages = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.page'));
const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prevBtn');
const nextBtn = document.getElementById('nextBtn');
const pageCounter = document.getElementById('pageCounter');
const pageIndicator = document.getElementById('page-indicator');

function updateUI() {
  pageCounter.textContent = `${current + 1} of ${TOTAL}`;
  pageIndicator.textContent = `${current + 1} / ${TOTAL}`;
  prevBtn.disabled = current === 0;
  nextBtn.disabled = current === TOTAL - 1;
}

function goToPage(newPage) {
  if (isAnimating || newPage < 0 || newPage >= TOTAL || newPage === current) return;
  isAnimating = true;

  const outPage = pages[current];
  const inPage = pages[newPage];

  inPage.classList.remove('hidden');

  if (newPage > current) {
    outPage.classList.add('flipping-out');
    setTimeout(() => {
      inPage.classList.add('flipping-in');
      outPage.classList.remove('flipping-out');
      outPage.classList.add('hidden');
      setTimeout(() => {
        inPage.classList.remove('flipping-in');
        isAnimating = false;
      }, 620);
    }, 300);
  } else {
    inPage.style.zIndex = 10;
    inPage.classList.add('flipping-in');
    setTimeout(() => {
      outPage.classList.add('hidden');
      inPage.classList.remove('flipping-in');
      inPage.style.zIndex = '';
      isAnimating = false;
    }, 620);
  }

  current = newPage;
  updateUI();
}

function nextPage() { goToPage(current + 1); }
function prevPage() { goToPage(current - 1); }

function setTheme(theme) {
  document.body.className = theme === 'dark' ? 'dark' : '';
  document.getElementById('btn-dark').classList.toggle('active', theme === 'dark');
  document.getElementById('btn-light').classList.toggle('active', theme === 'light');
}

// Keyboard navigation
document.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
  if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowDown') nextPage();
  if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' || e.key === 'ArrowUp') prevPage();
});

// Touch/swipe support
let touchStartX = 0;
document.addEventListener('touchstart', e => { touchStartX = e.touches[0].clientX; }, {passive: true});
document.addEventListener('touchend', e => {
  const diff = touchStartX - e.changedTouches[0].clientX;
  if (Math.abs(diff) > 50) {
    if (diff > 0) nextPage();
    else prevPage();
  }
}, {passive: true});

updateUI();
</script>
</body>
</html>
